Use Vector Search in Generative AI, Automation, and Analytics Tools

With unstructured data and vector search, you can ground your generative AI, automation, and analytics tools with relevant, customer-specific data to deliver results that align with usersâ€™ intent or contexts. To get started with vector search, you first build search index configurations from existing unstructured data.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Professional, Performance, and Unlimited editions.

When: This feature is available starting in June 2024.

How: Search index configurations break unstructured data into chunks to prepare it for vector search. Vector embeddings are then generated from those chunks. The vectorized content, stored in the Data Cloud search index, is searchable from and can be used in Einstein gen AI applications (Prompt Builder and Einstein Copilot), as well as automation (Flow Builder) and analytics (Tableau) applications. From Data Cloud, go to the Search Index page and create a search index configuration using either Easy Setup or Advanced Setup.
